SEC. 4.

Powers and duties of the Board.

âThe Board is vested with the authority, conformably with the provisions of this Act, to:

Administer the provisions of this Act;

Administer oaths in connection with the administration of this Act;

Issue, suspend or revoke certificates of regisÂtration for the practice of geodetic engineering;

Study the conditions affecting geodetic engiÂneering courses and training and the practice of the geodetic engineering profession in the Philippines, and exercise the powers conferred upon it by this and other Acts with a view to the maintenance of efficient, ethical, technical, moral and professional standards in the practice of geodetic engineering;

Study and examine, in cooperation with the Department of Education, the facilities of schools, colleges or universities seeking permission to open courses or already offering courses in geodetic engineering to see to it that the essential requirements, including the employment of qualified faculty members, are properly complied with;

SEC. 5.

Qualification of Board Members.â

Each member of the Board must, at the time of his appointment, be:

A citizen and resident; of the Philippines;

At least thirty-one years of age and of good moral character;

A registered geodetic engineer under this Act;

Actually in active practice of the Geodetic EnÂgineering or Surveying profession for at least ten years in or outside of the government service;

Not a member of the faculty of any school, institute, college or university where a regular course in Geodetic Engineering or Surveying is taught, or if he has been such a faculty member, he has stopped teaching therein for at least three consecutive years immediately preceding his appointment; and

Not pecuniarily interested, directly or indirectly, in any school, institute, college or university where a regular course in Geodetic Engineering is taught.

SEC. 29.

Penal Provisions

.âThe following shall be punished by a fine of not less than two hundred pesos nor more than five thousand pesos, or by imprisonment for not less than six months nor more than six years, or both, in the discretion of the Court:

Any person not exempt from registration who shall practice geodetic engineering in the Philippines within the meaning of this Act, without holding a valid certificate of registration issued in accordance with this Act;

Any person who shall give any false or frauduÂlent statement to the Board in order to obtain a certificate of registration as geodetic engineer;

Any person who shall present or use as his own a certificate of registration issued to another under this Act;

Any person who shall use a revoked or susÂpended certificate of registration as geodetic engineer;

Any person who shall assume, use or advertise as geodetic engineer, or append to his name, letters or words tending to convey the impression that he is a registered geodetic engineer when in fact he is not duly registered with the Board as such;

Any geodetic engineer, or any person on his behalf, who shall stamp or seal any document with his seal after his certificate of registration has expired or has been suspended or revoked;

Any geodetic engineer who shall sign his name, affix his seal, or use any other method of signature on plans, technical descriptions, or other documents prepared by or under another geodetic engineer's supervision, unless the same is prepared in such a manner as to clearly indicate the part or parts of such work actually performed by the former;

Any person, except the geodetic engineer in charge, who shall sign for any branch of the purveying work, or any function or surveying practice not actually performed by him; and

Any person who shall violate any provision of this Act.
